kets. Ireland’s ‘goldrush’ labour market created a seemingly endless demand for new labour. To understand how Irish firms utilised the new migrant workforce, the book also draws on interviews with employers. It thus locates the actions of both sides of the employment relationship in the particular socio-economic context in Ireland post-2004.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aForeign workersxHistoryx21st centuryxIreland. 0aForeign workerszIrelandxHistoryy21st century. 0aPolish peoplexIreland. 0aPolish peoplezIreland. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  aEurope.  aIreland.  aPolish migration.  aQualitative Panel Study.  acareers.  amobilities.1 aBobek, Alicja, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKrings, Torben, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMoriarty, Elaine, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aMoriarty, Elaine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSalamonska, Justyna, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aSalamońska, Justyna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWickham, James, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aWickham, James, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez978311128363040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152611157940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526111579423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526111579/original  a978-3-11-128363-0  Manchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagec1986d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles